init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The 92nd little pig said, "I'm not afraid of you."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I'm going to huff and puff and blow your house in.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The 92nd little pig said, "I don't think so, wolf.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When the wolf was waiting, Felicia called the 92nd little pig's friends, the 91st little pig and the 90th little pig

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was very angry, and he was going to eat them too.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was so angry, he forgot about Felicia.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was picked up, and the pigs flew away.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf tried to bite the pigs, but they were too high up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf tried to jump up, but he was too heavy.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was very angry, but he couldn't do anything.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was very angry, but he knew that the pigs were right.
